  <description type="morphology">Stem leaves appressed to weakly spreading when dry, long-lanceolate, abruptly broadened, oval; costa usually long-excurrent as a straight or flexuose, often fragile subula; proximal cells usually quadrate; distal laminal cells usually smooth, quadrate, with angular lumens, distal lamina rarely 2-stratose in patches; gemmae very rare.  Peristome teeth short and straight to long and twisted.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature summer–fall.</description>
